'''Kotohira Shrine''' (Kotohira-jinja) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shrine]] located in [[:en:Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki Prefecture]], [[:en:Minami-Matsuura District, Nagasaki|Minamimatsuura District]], [[:en:Shin-Kamigotō|Shinkamigotō]], and {{ill|Mikano-ura|ja|三日ノ浦郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mikano-ura|qq=}}.
== Deity == It enshrines {{ill|Ōmononushi|ja|大物主命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmononushi|qq=}} as its principal deity, and also enshrines two deities, {{ill|Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|lt=Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=}} and {{ill|Kanayama-hiko and Kanayama-hime|lt=Kanayama-hiko and Kanayama-hime|lt=Kanayamahiko|ja|金山彦命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanayamahiko|qq=}}, through {{ill|Joint Enshrinement|ja|合祀|1=co-Enshrinement|2=ja|3=合祀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Joint Enshrinement|13=User:Immanuelle/co-Enshrinement|qq=}}.
== History == [[File:IMG_mika1.JPG|180px|thumb|Shrine building]] The founding date is unknown. In ancient times, the shrine was known by the name '''Sannō Gongen-sha''', but after either being called '''Mikka Sannō''' or following the joint enshrinement of Kotoshironushi and Kanayamahiko, it came to be known as '''Ebisu Shrine'''. Moreover, as this shrine served as the head shrine for {{ill|Arakawa District|ja|荒川郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arakawa District|qq=}} and {{ill|Yodake Hie Shrine|ja|雄嶽日枝神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yodake Hie Shrine|qq=}}, and was enshrined on a subsidiary peak to the west of the Arakawa/Sannō mountains, it is presumed that it also enshrined their [[:en:Bunrei|Bunrei]].
On May 5, {{ill|1875|ja|1875|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1875|qq=}} (the 7th year of the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] era), it was classified as an {{ill|Unranked Shrine|ja|無格社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unranked Shrine|qq=}}, and in the 14th year ({{ill|1882|ja|1882|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1882|qq=}}) it was renamed '''Kotohira Shrine'''.
== Rites == Although the shrine is located in the former {{ill|Shinkamigotō|ja|上五島町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkamigotō|qq=}}, due to the fact that the priests of [[:en:Kagura|Kagura]]-less shrines at {{ill|Arakawa District|ja|荒川郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Arakawa District|qq=}} and {{ill|Yodake Hie Shrine|ja|雄嶽日枝神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yodake Hie Shrine|qq=}} are in charge, there is no offering of {{ill|Shinkamigotō Kagura|ja|上五島神楽|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinkamigotō Kagura|qq=}}.
; Major Festivals and Rituals * {{ill|Annual Festival|ja|例大祭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Annual Festival|qq=}} (November 24–25)
{{-}}
== Other Shrines == Among the other shrines in Mikano-ura, there is a '''Yama Shrine'''. In addition, in the adjacent {{ill|Aikawa District|ja|相河郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aikawa District|qq=}} there is a '''{{ill|Hime Shrine|ja|姫神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hime Shrine|qq=}}''', and in {{ill|Imazato District|ja|今里郷|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imazato District|qq=}} there is a '''{{ill|Ōyamatsumi Shrine|ja|大山祇神社 (新上五島町今里郷)|lt=Ōyamatsumi Shrine|lt_ja=大山祇神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōyamatsumi Shrine|qq=}}'''.
